The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, July 9: India?s foreign exchange (forex) reserves declined by $1.44 billion for the week ended July 1 to $137.443 billion. The fall was due to revaluation of international currencies, including the dollar, according to the Reserve Bank of India. The foreign currency assets declined by $1.516 billion to $131.426 billion.

 New Delhi, July 9: The Reserve Bank of India has disallowed foreign institutional investors (FIIs) from buying any further stake in Hindustan Petroleum Corporation Ltd (HPCL) without its prior approval. The foreign institutional investment in the public sector oil refinery company has already reached 22 per cent.

 Chennai, July 9: The Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI) today said the government should remove restrictions on domestic firms before opening up the accounting services sector for foreign direct investment. It has asked the government to allow limited liability partnership in the country.




